Package org.odpi.openmetadata.repositoryservices.enterprise.repositoryconnector.executors

package org.odpi.openmetadata.repositoryservices.enterprise.repositoryconnector.executors
The executors issue a request to one or more metadata repositories. They store their results in an accumulator and so can be cloned to operate across multiple threads - where there would be an executor for each thread that is executing a request.

    org.odpi.openmetadata.repositoryservices.enterprise.repositoryconnector.accumulators
    The accumulators are thread-safe caches of types and instances from the open metadata repositories that are building a list of unique results.
    org.odpi.openmetadata.repositoryservices.enterprise.repositoryconnector.control
    The federation control classes manage the process of interacting with a collection of metadata repositories.
